                            <comment id="13133497" author="grgrzybek" created="Tue, 24 Nov 2015 14:35:50 -0500"  >&lt;p&gt;After checking what can be done, after analyzing real world &lt;tt&gt;bin/setenv&lt;/tt&gt;, I&apos;ve decided to change custom &lt;tt&gt;SetEnvResolver&lt;/tt&gt; to special implementation - that takes user&apos;s version in case of conflict, so:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;if the (git) merge doesn&apos;t end with conflict (like BOTH_MODIFIED), then we&apos;re fine&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;if there&apos;s a conflict, we decide to stay with what user had before patching&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;IMO this is good assumption, because we don&apos;t plan making large changes to &lt;tt&gt;bin/setenv&lt;/tt&gt;, even if we increase memory reqs (like we did between 6.2.0 and 6.2.1), then conflict occurs only if user had own changes - which, by very great chance, include memory increase too.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;tt&gt;setenv&lt;/tt&gt;-like scripts are well known way of customizing products. For example, Apache Tomcat doesn&apos;t ship default &lt;tt&gt;setenv&lt;/tt&gt; script, but reads/sources one if such file is found.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;PR: &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/jboss-fuse/fabric8/pull/485&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/jboss-fuse/fabric8/pull/485&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
